  "text": "A broad panel of monoclonal antibodies was used to recognize surface antigens regulated during induction of cell maturation. It comprised CD11a, CD11b, CD11c and CD18, members of the ß2 family of leukocyte integrins; CD71, or transferrin receptor, expressed by most proliferating cells; CD14, the lipopolysaccharide receptor; CD34, a glycoprotein present on hematopoietic precursor cells; CD33, a marker for colonyforming units for granulocytes, erythrocytes, monocytes, and megakaryocytes; CD13, an antigen present during the early phase of myeloid commitment; CD41a which reacts with glycoprotein IIb complexed with gpIIIa to form the main fibrinogen receptor, expressed by megakaryocytes and platelets, and glycophorin A, a transmembrane sialoglycoprotein expressed by erythroid cells [CITATION_1] .",
